 can know about the status of your car service as well as much additional information to keep you updated.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Safety_check-ups_at_Car_Service_Centres\"><\/span>Safety check-ups at Car Service Centres<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Car Service Centres make sure that your car is safe and all safety features like <strong>ABS with EBD<\/strong>, <strong>Side and curtain airbags, Blind spot warning, and other little problems which can be dangerous if ignored.<\/strong><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"ABS_with_EBD\"><\/span>ABS with EBD<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>One of the most reliable Safety Features is ABS (Anti Braking System) it is a type of Active braking system which prevents our vehicles from skidding on the road due to which we lose control over the vehicle. ABS works when we suddenly apply breaks in any case.<\/p>\n<p>ABS repairing is a tough job but normally we get it replaced if there is any problem in ABS which makes it easy when we visit the car service centre.<\/p>\n<p>Its Mandatory for cars and bikes to have ABS.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Air_Bags\"><\/span>Air Bags<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Yes, it&#x2019;s very unlucky for a driver who might face a situation in which the Air Bags open. Still, it&#x2019;s one of the best life-saving features which is also made compulsory in cars.<\/p>\n<p>Side and curtain airbags provide extra protection to passengers in the back seat in case of major accidents from the side pillars and when something it&#x2019;s the car sideways.<\/p>\n<p>Air Bags can only be used once and if done will have to be replaced.<\/p>\n<p>Making it easier for the car mechanic and service centres.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span>Conclusion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Thinking about the future of car service centres we can say that we ar